' @id(USE-SESSION-BRIEF)
' @desc(USE-SESSION-BRIEF, "At session start a Claude Code SessionStart hook runs `mdd context`, handing the agent a compact whole-map table of contents (concepts grouped by kind, read from .mdd/map) plus the map-status freshness verdict — so the agent begins already oriented to what the system contains and whether the diagrams can be trusted. Realized by SEQ-SESSION-BRIEF; owned by CMP-SESSION-CLI (the command) and CMP-INIT-HOOK (the wiring).")
' @id(USE-DIAGRAMS-FIRST)
' @desc(USE-DIAGRAMS-FIRST, "The mdd init entrypoint (CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md) directs every agent to a diagrams-first reading order: run mdd context, and if FRESH read the diagrams and follow trace.yml source_links to the code before acting; if STALE re-map the drifted area with /mdd-map FIRST, then read. Realized by SEQ-DIAGRAMS-FIRST; owned by CMP-ENTRYPOINT-DIRECTIVE.")
' Objective use cases for agent session bootstrap (cycle 0014): surface a
' trustworthy model briefing at session start and make the agent consult the
' model before the code.
title Agent session bootstrap — use cases (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Agent (Claude / Codex)" as Agent <<missing>>

rectangle "mdd toolchain" {
  usecase "Receive map TOC +\nfreshness brief at\nsession start" as Brief
  usecase "Follow diagrams-first\nreading order\n(fresh: read / stale: remap)" as First
}

Agent --> Brief
Agent --> First
Brief ..> First : <<include>>

note bottom of Brief
  USE-SESSION-BRIEF: SessionStart hook -> `mdd context`
  prints the whole-map TOC + the map-status verdict.
  Realized by SEQ-SESSION-BRIEF; owned by CMP-SESSION-CLI
  + CMP-INIT-HOOK.
end note

note bottom of First
  USE-DIAGRAMS-FIRST: the entrypoint directive encodes
  fresh -> read + follow source_links / stale -> /mdd-map
  the drifted area first. Realized by SEQ-DIAGRAMS-FIRST;
  owned by CMP-ENTRYPOINT-DIRECTIVE.
end note
@enduml
